{{see|Grace|Graces|grâce}}
Grace is '''enabling power''' sufficient for progression. Grace divine is an indispensable gift from god for development, improvement, and character expansion. Without uniting with grace, there are certain limitations, weaknesses, flaws, and faults (i.e. carnality) humankind cannot overcome. Therefore, it is necessary to increase in grace - for added perfection, completeness, and flawlessness.

==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[#Old French|grace]]'' (modern ''[[grâce]]''), from Latin ''[[gratia]]'', from ''[[gratus]]'' ‘pleasing’.  Compare ''[[grateful]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/greɪs/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪs|-eɪs]]
{{rfap|US|UK}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

#{{uncountable}} [[elegant|Elegant]] [[movement]]; [[poise]] or [[balance]].
#{{uncountable}} {{theology}}: Free and [[undeserve]]d [[favour]], especially of [[God]].
#{{countable}} Short [[prayer]] of [[thank]]s before or after a [[meal]].
#:''It has become less common to say '''graces''' before having dinner.''

